        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 9:29PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 929 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edmondson, or 10 miles west of West Memphis, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mound City, Kate, Jericho, Browns, Louise, Jonquil, West Memphis,
Gammon, Brice, Cunningham Corner, Amanea, Edmondson, Clarkedale,
Tarsus, Wyandoke, St Clair, Harvard, Neuhardt, Simsboro, and
Democrat.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for eastern
Arkansas...and west Tennessee.</instruction>
